!
! Title: NichtTube's Star Citizen Allowlist
! Description: Minimal allowlist for Star Citizen (RSI Launcher + game client + Easy Anti-Cheat + Epic Online Services). Override for aggressive blocklists that break login, patching or server join (ClientTimeout / 15006 / 30000 / EOS_NoConnection).
! Version: 1.0
! Homepage: https://github.com/NichtTube/DNS_Blocklists_NichtTube
! Last modified: 16.05.2026
! Syntax: AdGuard
!
! USAGE NOTE
! Symptom this list fixes: Launcher logs in fine but the game cannot
! join servers, or EAC fails to initialise. Root cause is usually that
! the EAC module CDN (on.epicgames.com) and the EOS SDK auth endpoint
! (api.epicgames.dev) are DNS-blocked by privacy / tracking blocklists.
!
! Star Citizen ALSO needs direct UDP/TCP to RSI game servers:
!   TCP 8000-8020, UDP 64090-64110
! Those are NOT DNS-routed and cannot be fixed by an allowlist - check
! your firewall / router / ISP if you suspect those are blocked.
!
! This list deliberately does NOT allowlist epicgames.com broadly.
! Only the EAC/EOS-specific parent domains are exempted, so that
! Epic Games Store tracking on www.epicgames.com etc. stays blocked.
!
# === RSI / Cloud Imperium core (REQUIRED) ===
# Covers login, launcher API, patcher manifest, install endpoints,
# Spectrum and public.universe.robertsspaceindustries.com.
@@||robertsspaceindustries.com^$important
@@||cloudimperiumgames.com^$important
@@||turbulent.ca^$important

# === Easy Anti-Cheat backend (REQUIRED since Alpha 3.15.1) ===
# Without these: EAC blocks login, server join fails silently.
# - easyanticheat.net : hydra / gossip backend (heartbeat + status)
# - easy.ac           : short alias domain
# - eac-cdn.com       : legacy CDN, still serves older module URLs
@@||easyanticheat.net^$important
@@||easy.ac^$important
@@||eac-cdn.com^$important

# === Epic Online Services (REQUIRED for EAC since Epic acquisition) ===
# - on.epicgames.com : modules-cdn.eac-prod.on.epicgames.com
#                      (current EAC module download CDN)
# - epicgames.dev    : api.epicgames.dev
#                      (EOS SDK platform config + telemetry)
# Symptom if blocked: EOS_NoConnection in EasyAntiCheat logs.
@@||on.epicgames.com^$important
@@||epicgames.dev^$important
@@||datarouter.ol.epicgames.com^$important

# === DELIBERATELY NOT INCLUDED ===
# epicgames.com    - too broad. Epic Games Store tracking lives under
#                    www.epicgames.com, tracking.epicgames.com etc.
#                    EAC + EOS use the scoped subdomains above, not
#                    the apex epicgames.com - keep tracker blocks intact.
# *.cloudfront.net - CIG ships game patches via Amazon CloudFront with
#                    dynamic distribution IDs. Standard DNS blocklists
#                    don't block *.cloudfront.net at the apex anyway.
#                    If patching stalls, allowlist the specific
#                    distribution per-client, not the wildcard.
# *.amazonaws.com  - same logic as cloudfront.net.
#
# If a future SC build adds a new auth / telemetry domain not covered
# here, check the launcher log:
#   %LOCALAPPDATA%\rsilauncher\logs\
# and the EAC log:
#   <SC install>\LIVE\EasyAntiCheat\Logs\
